<unicode_normalization_guide>
<title>UNICODE SECURITY VULNERABILITIES</title>

<critical>Unicode normalization and character handling create unique security vulnerabilities. Attacks include homograph attacks (IDN), normalization form bypasses, fullwidth character substitution, case mapping issues, and invisible character injection. These can bypass security filters, enable phishing, and cause logic errors.</critical>

<scope>
- Homograph attacks (IDN)
- Normalization form bypasses (NFC, NFD, NFKC, NFKD)
- Width attacks (fullwidth characters)
- Case mapping vulnerabilities
- Invisible character injection
- Encoding confusion
- Unicode canonicalization
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify input processing that uses Unicode.
2. Test normalization form handling.
3. Probe for homograph character acceptance.
4. Test case conversion vulnerabilities.
5. Check for invisible character handling.
6. Analyze string comparison logic.
</methodology>

