<encoding_confusion>
<encoding_attacks>
{% raw %}
# Encoding-related attacks:

# UTF-8 overlong encoding (legacy):
# 'A' normal: 0x41
# Overlong 2-byte: 0xC1 0x81
# Overlong 3-byte: 0xE0 0x81 0x81
# Modern parsers reject, but legacy may accept

# Invalid UTF-8 sequences:
# 0xFF 0xFE (not valid UTF-8)
# May cause parser errors or bypass

# Encoding detection confusion:
# Mix UTF-8 and Latin-1 in same document
# Parser may misinterpret

# Double encoding:
# %252F = %2F (after decode) = / (after second decode)

# Character set mismatch:
# Declared: ISO-8859-1
# Actual: UTF-8
# Byte 0xC2 0xA0 (UTF-8 NBSP) 
# Interpreted as two Latin-1 chars
{% endraw %}
</encoding_attacks>

